### 2. Sections

Select sections you want to use from the list below, copy their code, and paste them in the text file inside
the `<body>` tags, after `<!-- YOUR SECTIONS GO HERE -->`. Click the arrows to expand.

### 3. Fill

Locate the tags similar to `<!-- WRITE THE TEXT HERE -->` and fill them with your text contents.

<details>
<summary><strong>TIPS</strong> (Click to expand)</summary>

1. If the `<!-- WRITE THE TEXT HERE -->` tag is enclosed in `<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>`, or `<a>`, write the text content
   directly.

---

2. If the `<!-- WRITE THE BODY HERE -->` tag is enclosed in `<td>`, paste each paragraph enclosed in `<p>`.

```html

<td>
    <p>Paragraph 1</p>
    <p>Paragraph 2</p>
    <p>Paragraph 3</p>
</td>
```

---

3. If you want to add section titles to your body sections, use `<h3>`.

```html
<h3>Section Title</h3>
```

---

4. If you want to style a piece of text, enclose that text in:
    1. `<strong>Text</strong>` for **BOLD**.
    2. `<i>Text</i>` for *ITALIC*.
    3. `<u>Text</u>` for <u>UNDERLINE</u>.

---

5. If you want to add a link, add `<a href=""></a>`. This is the same as buttons already in the sections. To use them,
   write the URL in the `href="HERE"`, and the normal text between the `<a>HERE</a>`. Fill the buttons the same way. If
   you want to remove buttons from the Banner sections, just delete the `<a></a>` tags.

---

6. For `<img>` tags, find the image file you want to use, go to [BASE64 Image](https://www.base64-image.de), select the
   image file you want to use, click <u>show code</u>, copy the text under the title **"For use in `<img>` elements:"**,
   and paste it in the `src="HERE"`.

```html
<img src="data:image/png;base64,..." alt="">
```
</details>

### 4. Send

Your e-mail is complete! Just hit send.

Note: If you want to preview your e-mail to see how it turned out, you can use [Online HTML Editor](https://www.onlinehtmleditor.net).

If you want to take a look at some pre-made examples [look at our samples](/templates/samples).
